 Ammonite, including provenance, language, onomastics, paleography, and iconography, has advanced considerably. In addition, the number of known inscriptions has increased. This updated edition includes 254 additional inscriptions, four new appendixes, and in many cases, new and improved images.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAmmonite languagevTexts. 0aInscriptions, Ammonite. 0aSeals (Numismatics)zJordan. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aAmmonite.  aAncient Jordan.  aIron Age Epigraphs.  aNear Eastern Inscriptions.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781646022687?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781646022687423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781646022687/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles